  forge/docs/functional-spec.md:109:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |
  forge/docs/functional-spec.md:111:| **Chunked dynamic-access workflow** | Dynamic-access generation mode for oversized `library-new-request` and `library-update-request` issues. `forge_metadata.py` owns the class threshold decision and passes the current chunk size to the workflow. The workflow processes at most that many uncovered classes, publishes that chunk, then resumes after the chunk PR merges. PR linking rules are in §WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking. |
