update-request` issues. `forge_metadata.py` owns the class threshold decision and passes the current chunk size to the workflow. The workflow processes at most that many uncovered classes, publishes that chunk, then resumes after the chunk PR merges. PR linking rules are in §WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:170:  If the current dynamic-access report has more uncovered classes than this\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:450:mode. If the current report has more uncovered dynamic-access classes than the\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:455:class count. For example, with threshold `5` and `7` uncovered classes, the\nforge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/codex_after_success.md:4:- Read the current test file to determine which `{library}` features are already covered.\nforge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/codex_after_success.md:5:- Identify additional uncovered features of `{library}` and add tests for it.\nforge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/basic_after_success.md:3:- Identify a new, functional feature of the library `{library}` that is not yet covered by the existing tests, and write tests for it.\nforge/docs/benchmarking.md:49:- Dynamic-access coverage, including covered calls, total calls, coverage\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:61:            \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:84:                \"iteration {current}/{max} — {uncovered} uncovered across {classes} classes\".format(\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:87:                    uncovered=current_report.total_calls - current_report.covered_calls,\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:88:                    classes=sum(1 for c in current_report.classes if c.uncovered_calls > 0),\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:93:            iteration_progress = \"- Iteration: {current}/{max}\\n- Overall coverage: {covered}/{total}\".format(\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:96:                covered=current_report.covered_calls,\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:163:                \"Optimistic dynamic-access coverage ({covered}/{total})\".format(\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:164:                    covered=current_report.covered_calls,\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:178:            if current_report.total_calls == current_report.covered_calls:\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:179:                self._print_message(\"all call sites covered\")\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:259:            \"report: {covered}/{total} covered\".format(\nforge/ai_workflows/core/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:260:                covered=report.covered_calls,\nforge/prompt_templates/issue_requested_metadata/issue-requested-metadata.md:17:- Treat every inferred reporter-requested metadata need as mandatory, even when dynamic-access coverage is already complete or the need is unrelated to an uncovered dynamic-access class.\nforge/prompt_templates/after-failed-iteration/basic_after_fail.md:2:Pick a different uncovered `{library}` feature and write tests for it.\nforge/prompt_templates/initial/basic_initial.md:22:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\nforge/ai_workflows/drivers/add_new_library_suppo