[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering SecureRandom options**\n\nI’m exploring options for fast and deterministic SecureRandom. Using a new SecureRandom seems fine, and the native option might be okay too. A fixed seeded SecureRandom might need a specific class, which simplifies things. If I go with a one-to-one mapping, there could be a dynamic class with an underscore in its name, which I wonder about—should it go public? I need to check if the native test results are failing.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_016e6669546b55cd016a25cdc2628c81938b958952b36cca55\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJc3Hr2uyUKOiQTtdjIS35Sd4qSOfe49Q-D3_YpMC-mvEBEviTFuqu9g0rnKGrTQrgLR1xS496zOR_H-zFPGubeK8sXhTDU7HELhaYjvzlSOAKa6PUKP6jaMRz4EjettsRRz_J5TmstB7Ry2cZ7YnwZ5AsN87u6lgMqTBLn6QBkMRs4Jx7FBoOr3r8M8o9v4VTjChJrk3fEwFn915jzxl0L9RAf3xTdKjXiL4NfDIyl78PGCXS406doVn2_l4BFWkBT9o29Rfiwi3_CvxJZO8aLgjW2A-zUWtnngmTw4Olf2VOgJ_-0bs_oO3WySbd3E0MgHWnW1RIpr9z2Yp89rPitTFFWH-F90KLxGgvm3nXGEUv3T1CUGkT5LiH1x14cHWGH1zE3JN5joJL0mkVdCFcJgdlWE52r1rn9W417tZ7QJY7Iz_v3fo1W0Up8GEpe_iIwqwQhkOv5x_REdjo7HTuZvXcPe5NQir-EapF2qeMSvEjQl-8SVq9Qxq251nONQs-Pe2okUxY7UIRrNDB-RTMFDlXq33SrgB1RGL687pqpUVtUFq_lqqgOA9o4HGjSFajti0jStSrjRICsF6BbF9erMgCyJLDpc1o-yDjyKvy2HMgTJF2M2TqawSEin5ayrlX9gSq7w-Mfsb9d7eC39H22FbHCoXK9gh8cWFQrbHYU0pBqp-BkERV8VbQJC0QEhhGF2PaTeOu934l3DtPyXjAeY2CctlN0yukSdlYDQPazYEn4EIY43SbcO1gvxyrpfrjWO_1PBs0s6EFzoxWhBhhg830YtTRb63w4esXCJhjgfQFFzggghk7GRfo4xjaxfA0CRocNrXESI3tY-X97pnHxEj4kQ49FoUQe7gzf5HEaSjgfJRHXbpCEYrllmptu1DNY1k_wTyNVWLWY1KKby9xuHWwEMHfQ_x1ZjvkspbYU16-Ek964jszo_JTW7Iy8qVGfz9Fj4d10wK9M_qzUx23fODSXm9W8jNljjlbJHXFieodp8natuTd-ax7ojjko7TdyerUgz518G5liRfbiFJrsRqUTDp1reLiPmT2B1GXmkWCKbbeDK5kWV-ipMGxAT2sbxr7_sjXVYf7Q61tsDYjhT6EqfwOc6ns8sA9zb7PJL4y0E56XBwa_bEsyY7NWDI3bQXVfXfPZyYNg_ZsODsmfpnn_A3zy2pQqbEJS9Wos8uHRWXzLPHTIbW_16wuzHc_WLrVNz1iac-l04xXLwvEUDJ7w9MByqvmX0JV7D8o6ZjmJ5BraggkpyXKq